Ahead of the 2019 general election, Voice of Ogun Women (VOW) a non-partisan gender-based group would on  Tuesday January 29, host gubernatorial aspirants in Ogun State to a debate. Olufunke Fadugba, Chairperson, Publicity Committee of VOW, said the debate holds at Olusegun Obasanjo Presidential Library in Abeokuta. Fadugba said the 12 aspirants scheduled for the debate are expected to reel out their plans for the citizens and residents of the state  if elected, adding that the candidates were selected after an extensive online survey. She made known that the debate tagged: “Ogun Women Decide” would afford electorates in Ogun the opportunity to choose the candidate that would represent their interest better and bring various developments in the state.